news.title: Punjab & Haryana HC lens on panel for illegal work in Aravalis
news.para: Haryana would also be filing the current status of the constructions going on in the hills as well as in respect of the allegations made in petition filed before the high court.

news.title: Indore civic body demolishes four illegal row houses
news.para: ​​IMC officials said that the encroacher, identified as Mahendra Jain, was found to have constructed four row houses on the land in the layout of D-20, D-21 and D-22 in Sudama Nagar locality illegally, and also sold them to others on fake documents and permission from the corporation.

news.title: Kolhapur civic body appoints engineers to regularise gunthewari proposals
news.para: The Kolhapur Municipal Corporation (KMC) has appointed engineers from the town planning department to process the gunthewari proposals fast.As per the existing law, the state government has allowed the regularisation of the houses built on gunthewari plots before December 31, 2020.

news.title: Arunachal Pradesh cabinet approves tenancy bill to boost rental housing market
news.para: The Bill envisages striking balance on the rights of tenant and landlord and create an accountable and transparent ecosystem for renting of premises in disciplined and efficient manner.

news.title: Provide amenities while handing over properties, Trichy corporation tells realtors
news.para: ​The decision was taken to prevent residents from running from pillar to post seeking basic amenities for their areas including roads, street lights and stormwater drains even after a significant number of houses were built on the layouts.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Regularization of illegal buildings in R3 zone unlikely
news.para: ​The legislation, which is being referred to as the impact fee law, follows the Gujarat Regularisation of Unauthorised Development Act, 2011, under which illegal constructions could be legalized by paying a fee.

news.title: West Bengal government to auction six more Alipore plots
news.para: ​A source said that Mumbai-based Phonex group gave the highest bidding price of about Rs 410 crore and is likely to win the bid. Hidco had fixed a starting bid price of Rs 236.7 crore for the plot at Rs 42.3 crore per acre.

news.title: Tamil Nadu government offers 3.5 times market value of land for new airport
news.para: PWD minister E V Velu said the owners of immovable properties will get parcels of land on the periphery of the airport site and the government will extend financial assistance for construction of houses.

news.title: One nautical mile of air space around Supertech twin towers briefly unavailable on Aug 28
news.para: The Union Ministry of Civil Aviation has given its consent for this, the Noida Authority said as it oversaw preparations for demolition of the nearly 100-metre-tall twin towers on Sunday.

news.title: Supertech twin towers: Roads to stay diverted on Aug 28, Google maps to have updates
news.para: "While several routes especially those leading to twin towers will have diversions from morning till evening, the Noida-Greater Noida Expressway will stay closed between 2 pm and 3 pm," DCP (Traffic) Ganesh Saha said as he and DCP (Central Noida) Rajesh S briefed reporters about the preparations for August 28.

news.title: '150%' confident of safely pulling down Supertech twin towers: Utkarsh Mehta, Edifice Engineering
news.para: The Mumbai-based Edifice Engineering has partnered with South Africa's Jet Demolitions for the high-risk job that involves razing two high-rise structures in a manner that the residential towers at barely nine-metre distance do not get affected.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM reviews preparations for demolition of Supertech twin towers
news.para: Water tankers, sprinklers and smog guns will be used to clear the dust generated as a result of demolition. Sweeping machines will be installed on the roads within two kilometre radius of the buildings.

news.title: Accountability will be fixed, if not today then tomorrow: Noida Authority CEO
news.para: The Supertech twin towers case is also a lesson for government officials, the senior IAS officer said, as legal action has been initiated against 26 Noida Authority officials for their involvement in the project.

news.title: SC says Supertech's twin towers buyers will be refunded in full, asks IRP to deposit Rs 1 crore
news.para: The apex court also asked the Interim Resolution Professional (IRP) of the firm, facing insolvency proceedings, to deposit Rs one crore with the apex court registry.

news.title: Maharashtra: No new buildings within 1km of SGNP, says forest department
news.para: Following the gazette notification of 2016, the state had set up a monitoring committee headed by BMC’s additional municipal commissioner (Projects) to sanction development works in the ESZ around Sanjay Gandhi National Park.
